deck: A new villain who makes his way to Gotham while Jim Gordon is operating as the GCPD's Batman and was active even just after Zero Year in a case that remained unsolved by Bruce Wayne
description:
Mysterious new power-player in Gotham City. His ulterior motive remains a mystery as does his past, but with his arrival came a new wave of former crooks turned metahuman powerhouses such as Precious Precious, Gee Gee Heung, and Qi Tsu. He provides his "seeds" to a select few, acting as implants that once rooted inside the body will grant their hosts extraordinary superpowers at the cost of their lives.

Mr. Bloom is created by Scott Snyder and Greg Capullo and is described as representing the weeds and cracks that keep sprouting in society between different groups based on dissatisfaction with the status quo. Anyone with the right motivation could become Mr. Bloom. It is known that 5 years ago, right after Zero Year, Bloom sold Man-Bat based implants to Peter Duggio that resulted in his death.
name: Mr. Bloom

deck: A novelist who moved to New York to write his novel, and promptly went insane
description:
Origin

Nothing is known about Martin Shay. A novelist, he moved to New York in the early 1970s in an effort to write the next great American novel. He moved into a house that was also a Thin Place, where the barrier between the mundane and the extraordinary is thin.

Creation

Martin Shay was created by James Tynion IV, Ming Doyle, and Riley Rossmo. He made his first appearance in Constantine: The Hellblazer #2.

Major Story Arcs

The Hellblazer

Martin drops out of contact with friends and families for three weeks, and when he emerges it is with 3,000 pages of a novel that he doesn't remember writing, written in a language never before documented, illustrated despite the fact that he has no skill in art. When he attempts to share the novel with friends, he and those he shares it with are driven violently insane. His fate is unknown, he is presumed dead.

Powers and Abilities

Martin has no known superhuman powers or abilities.
name: Martin Shay

deck: Reclusive and bitter mutant who wants to help the position of mutants in the world.
description:
Major Story Arcs

Adrian is a mutant who attends Fontane College in Boston. He is a recluse, always wearing a jacket that says "MONSTER" on the back, but has two close friends, Helen Williams and Art Wagner.

Adrian has six fingers on each hand, and can see in infrared. However, he also has a degenerative nerve disorder, and can't control his body well. Helen and Art help build him an exo-skeleton that helps his body control, and also gives him enhanced strength.

However, all he cares about is playing the piano, which he is very good at.

Mutant hysteria is rising across the country. The college's students are against the hysteria, and see an opportunity to address it when both Senator Robert Kelly, author of the Mutant Registration Act, and the Beast, both happen to be coming to campus.

Adrian shows Beast around, but then has a seizure in his room that Beast is suspicious of, since he finds a crushed Walkman nearby. He doesn't know about Adrian's exo-skeleton, but does know about his six fingers.

After the Beast gives a comical speech, Adrian accuses him of being a Stepin' Fetchit for mutants. Beast is ashamed. Adrian feels that mutants with useless powers, like his, are ignored by super-heroes, and indeed are endangered by their public acts.

When Kelly gives his speech, Adrian attacks him, hoping to make a statement against his anti-mutant agenda, but instead only fans it. The Defenders stop him, but only by shorting out his exo-skeleton, which leaves him in a bad state.

Beast later helps Adrian, Helen, and Art start M.O.N.S.T.E.R. (Mutants Only Need Sensitivity, Tolerance, and Equal Rights) to combat Kelly and help mutants. M.O.N.S.T.E.R. is later briefly run across in X-Men and Generation X.
name: Adrian Castorp

deck: A mysterious figure in the New York occult community, and associate of the demon Neron
description:
Origin

Nothing is known about Mister Rumor, beyond rumours and hearsay that filter through the occult community in New York, where he typically resides. He may have been in Calcutta in the late 1990s, during which he may have engaged in cannibalism. At some point he came into the employ of Neron.

Creation

Mister Rumor was created by James Tynion IV, Ming Doyle, and Riley Rossmo. He made his first appearance in Constantine: The Hellblazer #2.

Major Story Arcs

The Hellblazer

Working for his employer, Mister Rumor manages the purchase of dozens of haunted and occult sites around New York. He approaches John Constantine, who is visiting some of the various occult sites his employer owns. Determining that he poses no threat to his employer, he directs Constantine to one of the Thin Places. He later helps Neron negotiate pacts with various demonic factions.

Powers and Abilities

Mister Rumor appears to be an immortal, possibly as a result of a pact with Neron; it is known that he has not physically aged in at least 30 years. He possesses unknown occult powers. He seems to be able to read the truth in people, and to see through illusions, though whether this is an inherent skill or a spell is unknown. He has a great deal of knowledge about Thin Places, where occult energy is strong and the paranormal bleeds through.

issue_credits.name: Midnight In the V.I.P. Room of Good and Evil

name: Mister Rumor
